import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='X', y='Y', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the range of values for X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.lmplot(x="X", y="Y", data=data, height=7, aspect=1.2)
    plt.title("What is the correlation between X and Y?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['X'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'mean: {data["X"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[data['Y'] > 0.5]
    sns.regplot(x='X', y='Y', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y for values greater than 0.5?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
